  "body": "`p2p` and `p2p/discover` packages tests sometimes fail on a 30 sec timeout.\r\nRunning in parallel with all other tests on the GH CI macOS VM can reproduce this.\r\n\r\nRunning them alone (`go test -count 1 ./p2p/...`) doesn't reproduce this (they take about 10 sec).\r\nIf we'd like to reduce the test timeout to 10 sec or less, this is too close.\r\nTry e.g. `go test -count 1 ./p2p/... -timeout 5s`\r\n\r\n## Top slow tests (values in ms):\r\nTestTable_ReadRandomNodesGetAll 3100\r\nTestBucket_bumpNoDuplicates 2170\r\nTestUPNP_DDWRT 2100\r\nTestUDPv4_smallNetConvergence 1690\r\nTestUDPv5_pingCall 1630\r\nTestFairMix 1570\r\nTestUDPv5_lookup 1250\r\nTestUDPv5_callTimeoutReset 1180\r\nTestUDPv5_talkRequest 940\r\nTestUDPv5_multipleHandshakeRounds 940\r\nTestDialSchedRemoveStatic 900\r\n\r\n## All slow tests (longer than 100ms):\r\nTestDialSchedResolve (0.30s)\r\nTestDialSchedNetRestrict (0.30s)\r\nTestDialSchedStaticDial (0.45s)\r\nTestDialSchedHistory (0.60s)\r\nTestDialSchedDynDial (0.60s)\r\nTestDialSchedRemoveStatic (0.90s)\r\nTestTable_ReadRandomNodesGetAll (3.10s)\r\nTestUDPv5_LocalNode (0.13s)\r\nTestUDPv4_pingTimeout (0.27s)\r\nTestUDPv4_findnodeTimeout (0.28s)\r\nTestUDPv5_callResend (0.29s)\r\nTestUDPv5_findnodeCall (0.29s)\r\nTestUDPv5_pingHandling (0.31s)\r\nTestUDPv5_talkHandling (0.31s)\r\nTestUDPv5_findnodeHandling (0.31s)\r\nTestUDPv5_unknownPacket (0.32s)\r\nTestUDPv5_lookupE2E (0.44s)\r\nTestTable_findNodeByID_examples (0.30s)\r\nTestUDPv5_talkRequest (0.94s)\r\nTestUDPv5_multipleHandshakeRounds (0.94s)\r\nTestUDPv5_callTimeoutReset (1.18s)\r\nTestUDPv5_lookup (1.25s)\r\nTestUDPv5_pingCall (1.63s)\r\nTestUDPv4_smallNetConvergence (1.69s)\r\nTestBucket_bumpNoDuplicates (2.17s)\r\nTestTestVectorsV5 (0.19s)\r\nTestIteratorClose (0.26s)\r\nTestIteratorNodeUpdates (0.10s)\r\nTestIteratorRootRecheckOnFail (0.13s)\r\nTestFairMix (1.57s)\r\nTestLocalNodeSeqPersist (0.20s)\r\nTestLocalNodeEndpoint (0.16s)\r\nTestAutoDiscRace (0.50s)\r\nTestUPNP_DDWRT (2.10s)\r\n\r\nFixing this means either optimizing individual tests or test groups (with mocking, caching, special config parameters etc.),\r\nor moving inherently slow tests under the \"integration\" test suite (`go:build integration`).\r\n",
